SIMPLE: repress
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repress
<hw>Re*press"</hw> <pr>(r?-pr?s")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>re-</ets> + <ets>press</ets>.]</ety> <def>To press again.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repress</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Repress
<hw>Re*press"</hw> <pr>(r?-pr?s")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>re- + press</ets>: cf. L. <ets>reprimere</ets>,
<ets>repressum</ets>. Cf. <er>Reprimand</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
press back or down effectually; to crush down or out; to quell; to
subdue; to supress; <as>as, to <ex>repress</ex> sedition or rebellion;
to <ex>repress</ex> the first risings of discontent.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to check; to restrain; to keep
back.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Desire of wine and all delicious drinks, . . . ⟦br⟧
Thou couldst <qex>repress</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To crush; overpower; subdue; suppress; restrain;
quell; curb; check.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repress</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Repress
<hw>Re*press"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of repressing.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Represser</ent>⟦br⟧
